CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 12, 1941 reads:"The sun shone and the guests were pleased and pleasing at the Eastern Open Golf Tournament in Pittsburgh last weekend. Courier photoman snapped there charming folks (left to right):...Mrs. Melba Rhodes, Mrs. Marian Cralle, Pittsburgh; Miss Billy Fortune, Suffolk, VA...-Photos by Teenie Harris."
TitMainTitle: Melba Rhodes wearing short sleeved dress with bow on back, Marian Cralle, and Billy Fortune seated behind railing at South Park golf course for the Eastern Open
